SIMPLE: cowpea
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cowpea
<hw>Cow"pea`</hw> <pr>(kou"p⟦emac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The seed of one or more leguminous plants of the genus
<gen>Dolichos</gen>; also, the plant itself. Many varieties are
cultivated in the southern part of the United States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A leguminous plant (<spn>Vigna
Sinensis</spn>, syn. <spn>Vigna Catjang</spn>) found throughout the
tropics of the Old World. It is extensively cultivated in the Southern
United States for fodder, and the seed is used as food for
man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowper's glands</ent>⟦br⟧
